        Official Singles Chart on 11/2/2022

        11 February 2022 - 17 February 2022

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        Here are some things to note about this week:
        • Top 10 debut for ArrDee & Aitch's highly anticipated collab War. I expected it to debut high. As for the song itself... it's fine. Wish it was a lot better, but I don't mind it.
        • Speaking of ArrDee, Flowers (Say My Name) has dropped out out of the Top 40, as has Make You Smile, My Universe & I Drink Wine. In the case of Flowers (Say My Name), thank God! The song is f**king awful & if I were to do a list of the worst UK hit songs of 2021, I'd place it at Number 8. I found both samples to be poorly used & I don't think I need to comment on the toxicity of the content. As for the other songs, it's a shame they've fallen; Make You Smile is the first time I've found myself really liking a D-Block Europe song. However, I can maybe see it rebounding after the video dropped, so that's good. Not much to say about My Universe, it sounds absolutely perfect & the performances are very good. And I Drink Wine is one of the best songs Adele has EVER made. The instrumental has a nice swell to it, as usual her performance is great & the writing is exceptional.
        • Liam Gallagher debuts in the top 20! I have a complicated opinion overall on Liam Gallagher & for that matter, Oasis. I'm conflicted on what I think of his new song. Instrumentally it's fine, but everything else I just don't really care.
        • Top 40 debuts for Tate McRae, Nicki Minaj & Lil Baby, Juice WRLD & Jax Jones featuring MNEK. Tate's song I actually quite like, which is odd because I'll admit... I absolutely hated you broke me first. I don't care if the lyrics were good or not, it was one of the worst sounding songs to have become a hit in the past 5 years & I absolutely hated Tate's voice. I was especially annoyed it made TWO UK year end lists in a row. So I'm surprised that I kinda like her new song. I'm still not on board at all with her voice, but the lyrics & the instrumental? they deliver. Nicki & Lil Baby's new track has some good flows & a nice synth line, but the production's very clumsy & there are some questionable lines. Can't expect much from Nicki, but I do expect better from Lil Baby, an artist I've grown to quite like over the past couple of years. Next is Juice WRLD & all I gotta say is these posthumous album rollouts are getting ridiculous now! It just feels very gross that Juice's legacy is becoming like that of XXXTentacion (& for the record, I never hated either of this artists when they were alive, they made some songs I did flatout enjoy). Is the good song? It's better than Already Dead at least, but I can't look past the fact his label is clearly trying to make some quick cash off his death & I can't respect it at all for that. And finally, there's Jax Jones' new song with MNEK. Musically, it's great & it's just a fun bouncy house track. If it sticks around, I'll be fine with it.
        • Numb Little Bug enters the top 40! Very pleased it has, as it's a very good track if I do say so myself. Fun instrumental & well thought out lyrics too. Not quite a fan of the vocals, but aside from that, very happy it's here.
        • Blinding Lights & Clash are back in! The former is destined to become a classic & rightfully so, because it's a great song, although you didn't need me to tell you that. Honestly though, I never really cared for Clash. The piano line, Stormzy & the beat switch up, they're all fine. But Dave puts in probably his most underwhelming performance ever & the production outside of the switch up is pretty bad. Pretty disappointing track, I expect a lot better from Dave.

        Edit: After hearing it a few more times, I'm now in love with she's all i wanna be by Tate McRae. It's a excellent song & I'm happy it could be her next big hit. Giving it Best of the Week for this week.
